text: Ulmanis (feminine: Ulmane) is a Latvian surname originated from the German surname Ullmann. Notable individuals with the surname include: * Kārlis Ulmanis (1877–1942), First Prime Minister of Latvia * Gunārs Ulmanis (1938–2010), Latvian footballer * Guntis Ulmanis (born 1939), President of Latvia (1993–1999)
title: Ulmanis
